      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with your <strong>balsamic sundried tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>to the pan with 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[260ml]</span> <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce is starting to thicken and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1683890956379-x200.jpg",
